    "updated_at": "2018-06-25T12:00:06Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Now that we have Clojure generated payment messages we can do the following:\r\n\r\n- Send a 1:1 message to the whisper id of the recipient after every successfully sent transaction, whether it was from Wallet Send or from Chat /send. If whisper id is not available (e.g. if the user pasted the address of a non-Status user), then no chat message is sent, which is fine.\r\n- Remove the `execute-stored-command` kludge since we only needed to continue the interrupted bot command code in order to send out the payment message. If it's done in the same way for both chat and wallet payments, we don't need this any more.\r\n- Clean up any other hotfixes we had in place because of \"message from previous payment shown\" bug.\r\n- Re-enable amount and symbol in Chat Send screen, again not constrained by the command code any more (review this decision with UX)",
